The paper discusses the implementation of physical layer network coding (PNC) in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the practical challenges of implementing PNC, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of Universal Software Radio Peripherals (USRPs) and orthogonal frequency division multiplexing (OFDM) also suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography (cs.CR).
